<div class="container">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-12">
			<h3>
				It's great that you're choosing to tell your story.
			</h3>
			<h3>
				Telling your story, even anonymously, helps you and your community stand
				together and raises awareness for your cause.
			</h3>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-8">
			<form role="form" action="/story" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
				<div class="form-group">
					<label for="title">What's your story about?</label>
					<input type='text' class="form-control" name='title' placeholder="Title" id="title-input" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="right" data-trigger="focus" data-html="true" data-content="<p>Choose a short but descriptive title for your story.</p><p>Don't worry about it too much at this stage: you can always come back to it later."/>
				</div>

				<div class="form-group">
					<label for="image1">Choose a photo</label>
					<input type='file' name='image1' id="image-input" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="right" data-trigger="hover focus" data-html="true" data-content="<p>Please submit a photo of yourself from chin down, as shown in the example.</p><img src='/images/example_crop.jpg' style='width: 50%;'></img><p><strong>Why?</strong> This provides a balance between anonymity and providing readers with an identity to rally behind.</p>"/>
					<!-- <input type='file' name='image2'/>
					<p class="help-block">
						Readers will see this second image when they
						navigate to your story's page.
					</p> -->
				</div>

				<div class="form-group">
					<label for="paragraphs">Tell your story</label>
					<textarea class="form-control" rows="20" name='paragraphs' id="story-input" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="right" data-trigger="focus" data-html="true" data-content="<p>Everyone has a story. Tell your story in any way that you like: there are people out there who will listen.</p><h5>Tips:</h5><ul><li>Anonymity is fine. The most important thing is to avoid putting anyone in danger.</li><li>Don't feel pressured to keep your story short. Try to fill the entire text area or more.</li></ul>"></textarea>
				</div>

				<div class="form-group">
					<label>Should we keep in touch?</label>
					<input type="email" class="form-control" name="email" placeholder="email (optional)" id="email-input" data-toggle="popover" data-placement="right" data-trigger="focus" data-html="true" data-content="<p>It's totally optional for you to give us your email.</p><p>However, if you give it to us:</p><ul><li>We promise to never to give it to anyone else.</li><li>We can help you keep track of your stories and their supporters</li><li>You will be able to edit your story later, should you wish to do so.</li></ul>">
				</div>

				<div class="form-group">
					<button type="submit" class="btn btn-default btn-block" style="margin-bottom: 100px;">Submit</button>
				</div>
			</form>
		</div>
	</div>

</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
$(function() {
	$('#title-input').popover();
	$('#image-input').popover();
	$('#story-input').popover();
	$('#email-input').popover();
});
</script>